Aristida ciliata

    Authority   Desf.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3370

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A densely caespitose grass. USES Used as a pasture
   grass and as a sand binder. GROWING PERIOD Perennial or annual grass
   depending on growing conditions. COMMON NAMES Nissi, Gau sullayyan,
   Qaba, Assah, Hmera, Hemlira, Hamareet, Lammati, Morokba, Ressasa,
   N'say, Soilane, Gharza. FURTHER INF Scientific synonym: Stripagrostris
   ciliata. Nissi is well adapted to stony or gravelly soils.

   Sources
   SOURCES (A. ciliata Desf. in Schrad.)
   Kernick M 1978 pp 355-370 [TEMP, DEP, RAIN, TEXT, DRA, SAL, USE]
   White F 1983 pp 141 204 221

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
